<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="33" pageNumber="48">
<bibRefCitation pageId="33" pageNumber="48">Desmarest (1848)</bibRefCitation>
assigned the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphecomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecomyia boscii" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boscii">Sphecomyia boscii</taxonomicName>
to the specimens Latreille used to establish 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphecomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphecomyia</taxonomicName>
. The name was forgotten until its rediscovery in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, NL" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="41" pageNumber="56" pagination="226 - 258" title="Type designations of genus-group names of Diptera given in d'Orbigny's Dictionnaire Universel d'Histoire Naturelle." url="https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/18916/ent_FCT_62.pdf" volume="30" year="1990">
<pageBreakToken pageId="34" pageNumber="49" start="start">Evenhuis</pageBreakToken>
and Thompson (1990)
</bibRefCitation>
. We do not assign a neotype as it is uncertain if the series is lost. It is not listed among the MNHN types, nor did the primary author encounter it during a visit to the collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="49">
COI barcoding recovered two clusters of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vittata" pageId="34" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="vittata">S. vittata</taxonomicName>
with a 
<taxonomicName genus="Criorhinina" lsidName="Criorhinina maximum" pageId="34" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="maximum">maximum</taxonomicName>
barcode divergence barcode of 2.41%. Specimens of both clusters were compared, and no morphological differences were found.
</paragraph>
